version: 1
display_name: VCFM-9X-000125 - The VMware Cloud Foundation vCenter VAMI Lighttpd service must protect system resources from hosted applications.
global_description: |-
  Most of the attention to denial-of-service (DoS) attacks focuses on ensuring that systems and applications are not victims of these attacks. However, these systems and applications must also be secured against use to launch such an attack against others.

  A variety of technologies exist to limit, or in some cases eliminate, the effects of DoS attacks. Limiting system resources that are allocated to any user to a bare minimum may also reduce the ability of users to launch some DoS attacks.

  One DoS mitigation is to prevent VAMI from keeping idle connections open for too long.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFM-9X-000125
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_vcenter_vami:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation vCenter VAMI Lighttpd service must protect system resources from hosted applications.
    control_id: VCFM-9X-000125
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command prompt, run the following:

      # /usr/sbin/lighttpd -p -f /etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf 2>/dev/null|grep "server.max-keep-alive-idle"

      Example result:

      server.max-keep-alive-idle=30

      If "server.max-keep-alive-idle" is not set to 30, this is a finding.

      Note: The command must be run from a bash shell and not from a shell generated by the "appliance shell". Use the "chsh" command to change the shell for the account to "/bin/bash". Refer to KB Article 2100508 for more details:

      https://knowledge.broadcom.com/external/article?legacyId=2100508
    rationale: |-
      Most of the attention to denial-of-service (DoS) attacks focuses on ensuring that systems and applications are not victims of these attacks. However, these systems and applications must also be secured against use to launch such an attack against others.

      A variety of technologies exist to limit, or in some cases eliminate, the effects of DoS attacks. Limiting system resources that are allocated to any user to a bare minimum may also reduce the ability of users to launch some DoS attacks.

      One DoS mitigation is to prevent VAMI from keeping idle connections open for too long.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/lighttpd/vhosts.d/applmgmt-lighttpd.conf

      Add or reconfigure the following value:

      server.max-keep-alive-idle = 30

      Restart the service with the following command:

      # systemctl restart lighttpd
